Repository: sophie
Description: A personal assistant that helps you manage your daily tasks and schedule.

Directory Structure:
- .github/: GitHub Actions configuration
- .github/workflows/: GitHub Actions workflows
- .venv/: Virtual environment for Python
- agents/: Prompts for the assistant agents in markdown format
- docs/: Documentation in Sphinx and markdown format
- docs/PRD.md: Product Requirements Document
- docs/ContentCategories.md: Content categories for the assistant for different requirements
- docs/Deploy.md: Deployment instructions for a DigitalOcean application
- docs/Design.md: Design documentation
- docs/Interfaces.md: Interfaces documentation API and CLI
- docs/LaunchPlan.md: Launch plan for the assistant
- docs/Monitoring.md: Monitoring and logging plan
- docs/ProjectPlan.md: Project plan for the assistant
- docs/Requirements.md: Requirements documentation
- docs/Runbook.md: Runbook for the assistant
- docs/Security.md: Security requirments
- docs/Telemetry.md: Telemetry plan
- docs/Testing.md: Testing plan
- node_modules/: Node.js modules
- public/: Public files for node.js and react application
- src/: Main application code
- src/__tests__/: Test files for the application
- src/components/: React components

Setup:
- Run `npm install` to install dependencies
- Use `npm run dev` for development
- Run `npm test` for testing

Guidelines:
- Follow ESLint configuration
- Write tests for all new features
- Use TypeScript for new code

Tool versions:
 node.js: x.x.x
 React: x.x.x
 Sphinx: x.x.x
 Typescript: x.x.x
 ESLint: x.x.x
 DigitalOcean application: x.x.x

